Colonies horizontally extended with determinate growth, composed of flat branches and short secondary branches, with frequent anastomosis; coenosteum sometimes filling the spaces between branches. Radial corallites appressed tubular to tubular, not touching but closely arranged laterally, rarely on top and undersides of branches. Coenosteum with dense elaborated spinules throughout (
Wallace, 1999
).

